0concern%20in%20AI%2C%20and%20Apple%20is%20addressing%20it%20head%20on.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20need%20to%20panic%20%E2%80%94%20Apple%20says%20it%20definitely%20didn't%20train%20its%20artificial%20intelligence%20on%20your%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivacy%20is%20a%20massive%20concern%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20AI%2C%20but%20Apple%20stayed%20true%20to%20its%20brand%20by%20prioritizing%20customer%20protection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlongside%20its%20introduction%20of%20Apple%20Intelligence%2C%20the%20tech%20giant%20announced%20that%20the%20system%20would%20operate%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-just-threw-down-gauntlet-in-ai-wars-intelligence-wwdc-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPrivate%20Cloud%20Compute%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20an%20infrastructure%20designed%20for%20handling%20AI%20requests%20privately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-wwdc-event-live-updates-keynote-announcements-2024-6%23bring-on-the-apple-intelligence-demos%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorldwide%20Developer%20Conference%20keynote%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Apple%20showed%20off%20impressive%20AI%20announcements%20like%20custom%20emojis%20called%20%26quot%3BGenmojis%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20more%20helpful%20Siri%2C%20and%20a%20partnership%20with%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-giants-openai-anthropic-running-out-of-good-training-data-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%20maker%20uses%20the%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20users'%20interactions%20with%20its%20services%20to%20train%20its%20models%2C%20Apple%20said%20that's%20not%20the%20case%20for%20iPhone%20owners.%20And%20while%20ChatGPT%20is%20coming%20to%20Apple%20products%20by%20way%20of%20a%20new-and-improved%20Siri%2C%20users%20have%20the%20option%20to%20opt%20out%20of%20using%20the%20tool%20from%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20do%20not%20use%20our%20users'%20private%20personal%20data%20or%20user%20interactions%20when%20training%20our%20foundation%20models%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20Apple%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmachinelearning.apple.com%2Fresearch%2Fintroducing-apple-foundation-models%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20note%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20Monday%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20it%20said%20its%20models%20are%20trained%20on%20licensed%20data%20and%20publicly%20available%20data%20collected%20by%20its%20web%20crawler%20called%20Applebot.%20It's%20up%20to%20web%20publishers%20to%20opt%20out%20of%20this%20if%20they%20don't%20want%20information%20on%20their%20site%20used%20for%20Apple%20Intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20company%20said%20that%20it%20applies%20%26quot%3Bfilters%20to%20remove%20personally%20identifiable%20information%20like%20social%20security%20and%20credit%20card%20numbers%20that%20are%20publicly%20available%2C%26quot%3B%20profanity%2C%20and%20other%20%26quot%3Blow-quality%20content%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20data%20it%20uses%20for%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20have%20found%20themselves%20in%20hot%20water%20over%20AI%20privacy%20concerns%20in%20the%20past.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EZoom%20users%20threatened%20to%20ditch%20the%20video%20conference%20company%20in%202023%20after%20taking%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20its%20terms%20and%20conditions.%20Part%20of%20the%20agreement%20said%20that%20users%20would%20consent%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzoom-terms-service-train-ai-calls-without-consent-privacy-backlash-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Zoom%20using%20their%20data%20for%20AI%20training%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20the%20backlash%2C%20the%20company%20added%20a%20line%20to%20its%20terms%20of%20service%20clarifying%20that%20users%20could%20choose%20not%20to%20have%20their%20data%20used%20for%20such%20purposes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20is%20setting%20a%20new%20standa